 greci, spesso neoattestati, come pharmacia. Il nuovo testo consente una lettura più genuina, con documentazione importante per filologi e storici della medicina.  aThis edition, with copious comments and notes, presents new insights into the writings of an author often cited already by the sources of Galen and by Marcellus. The discovery of several indirect witnesses has crucially extended the stemma codicum of the former Teubner text. This volume will be of great interest to Latin and Greek philologists and historians of medicine.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAntike Medizin. 4aRezeptsammlung. 4aScribonius Largus. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh  aAncient medicine.  aScribonius Largus.  acollection of recipes.1 aSconocchia, Sergio, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311043961840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311043091240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110430912423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110430912/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020